  <description type="morphology">Shrubs 10–70 cm.  Stems ascending.  Leaf blades linear to narrowly oblong, (2–)3–5 cm × 2–8 mm, abaxial surface white-hairy to white-velutinous, not glaucous, adaxial often white-hairy on base, petiole, and midvein, ± glaucous when young.  Pedicels recurved, pale-glaucous, seldom more than 6(–8) mm, rarely 2 times length of corolla.  Corymbs nodding, (2–)4–8-flowered, on curved branchlets.  Corollas 6(–8) × 5–6(–7) mm, not dilated basally.  Capsules obovoid to subglobose, 4–5.5 × 4 mm, glabrous or minutely hairy at base.  2n = 48.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Flowering May–Jul(–Sep); fruiting Jun–Sep</description>
